      • handle

        public void handle(Event e)
        Description copied from interface: Handler
        Handle the event in this instance. This is the second half of Event.dispatch(Handler). The method must invoke a concrete onXxx method for the given event, or invoke it's Handler.onUnhandled(Event) method if the EventType of the event is not recognized by the handler.

        Note: The handler is not supposed to invoke the Handler.handle(Event) method on it's Handler.children(), that is the responsibility of the Event.dispatch(Handler)

        Specified by:
        handle in interface Handler
        Parameters:
        e - The event to handle

        BaseHandler
